spec:
add a sample-quarkus-correlation module to the project
This should have a class that adds a filter to Quarkus:


import jakarta.ws.rs.container.ContainerRequestContext
import jakarta.ws.rs.container.ContainerRequestFilter
import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.Provider
import org.incept5.correlation.CorrelationId

@Provider
class CorrelationIdFilter : ContainerRequestFilter {

    override fun filter(requestContext: ContainerRequestContext) {
        // Get or create a new correlation ID
        val correlationId = requestContext.headers.getFirst("X-Correlation-ID") ?: CorrelationId.getId()

        // Set the correlation ID in the thread local context
        CorrelationId.setId(correlationId)

        // Add or update the correlation ID header in the request
        requestContext.headers.putSingle("X-Correlation-ID", correlationId)
    }
}

The sample quarkus app should also have the following in the application.yaml:
quarkus.log.level=INFO
quarkus.log.category."org.incept5".level=DEBUG

quarkus.log.console.format=%d{yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSSZ} %-5p %H -- [%X{traceId}/%X{spanId}/%X{correlationId}] - [%c{3.}] (%t-%t{id}) %s%e%n

quarkus.log.json.console.enable=true

Add a controller class that has a simple GET method and a log statement to show in the logs that the controller was invoked

Add a test in the sample-quarkus-correlation project that asserts that a CorrelationId is present in the logs when the endpoint is invoked
